    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-12-25T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-12-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="416"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/14287: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-25T12:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 25, 1938—noon.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 25—11:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>620. Embassy’s 613, December 23, 9 a.m. The First Secretary of the British
                    Embassy informed me December 24, 9 p.m., that Donald had informed him that
                    Chiang Kai Shek wished to state to the British <pb facs="0440" n="436"
                        xml:id="pg_436"/> and American Governments that nothing Wang Ching Wei might
                    do or say represented the Chinese Government in any way. Being unable to reach
                    me quickly Donald asked the British Secretary to transmit this message to me for
                    the Department.</p>
                <p>The Embassy is reliably informed that General Chiang returned to Chungking on the
                    afternoon of December 24 from his trip of inspection in the northwest.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Peiping for Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
